## Cyber Analytics Repository (CAR)

MITRE CAR (Cyber Analytics Repository) is a collection of detection analytics built around ATT&CK techniques.

CAR helps defenders translate ATT&CK intelligence into practical detections by providing:

- Detection logic
- Pseudocode
- SIEM query examples
- Detection rationale
- Validation guidance

Key takeaway:

ATT&CK explains **how attackers operate**, while CAR helps defenders understand **how to detect those activities**.

---

## MITRE D3FEND

MITRE D3FEND is a defensive framework that maps security controls and defensive techniques to adversary behaviour.

While ATT&CK focuses on attacker actions, D3FEND focuses on defensive countermeasures.

The framework is organized into defensive tactics such as:

- Harden
- Detect
- Isolate
- Deceive
- Evict
- Restore

D3FEND helps defenders understand:

- How specific controls work
- Which attacks they mitigate
- How defensive techniques relate to ATT&CK techniques

Example defensive concepts include:

- Credential Rotation
- User Behaviour Analytics
- Log Monitoring
- Network Isolation

---

## MITRE Caldera

MITRE Caldera is an automated adversary emulation platform.

It allows organizations to:

- Simulate real-world attacks
- Test detections
- Validate security controls
- Practice incident response
- Perform red and purple team exercises

Caldera uses ATT&CK techniques to replicate attacker behaviour in controlled environments.

---

## Adversary Emulation Plans

MITRE provides detailed adversary emulation plans that replicate known threat actor behaviour.

These plans help organizations:

- Test defenses realistically
- Measure detection coverage
- Improve threat-informed defense programs
- Validate security controls against real-world attack techniques

