## Emerging MITRE Frameworks

### AADAPT

AADAPT focuses on threats targeting digital asset ecosystems, including:

- Blockchain technologies
- Cryptocurrency platforms
- Digital wallets
- Smart contracts

The framework maps attacker tactics and techniques specific to digital asset environments.

### ATLAS

ATLAS focuses on threats targeting Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning systems.

It documents:

- AI-specific attack techniques
- Adversarial machine learning threats
- AI security weaknesses
- Defensive mitigations

As AI adoption grows, frameworks like ATLAS help defenders understand emerging risks.

---

## Key Takeaways

- MITRE ATT&CK provides a standardized framework for understanding attacker behaviour.
- Tactics represent attacker goals, while techniques describe how those goals are achieved.
- ATT&CK helps threat intelligence, SOC, detection engineering, incident response, and red team functions work from a common language.
- CAR translates ATT&CK techniques into practical detection analytics.
- D3FEND maps defensive controls to attacker behaviours.
- Caldera enables realistic adversary emulation and defensive testing.
- Threat actor profiling using ATT&CK helps organizations build more effective detections and threat hunting programs.
- Emerging frameworks such as AADAPT and ATLAS extend MITRE's coverage into digital assets, blockchain technologies, and AI security.

## SOC Analyst Perspective

Understanding MITRE ATT&CK provides a structured way to analyze alerts, investigate incidents, map attacker behaviour, identify defensive gaps, and communicate findings consistently across security teams. ATT&CK serves as one of the most important frameworks used in modern SOC operations, threat hunting, detection engineering, and incident response.
